# ============================================================================
# Nepal Grocery POS — append this block to the Pi's Caddyfile
# (the file bind-mounted into the Caddy container at /etc/caddy/Caddyfile).
#
# Served on a DEDICATED HTTPS PORT (8443) so it does not disturb the existing
# uk-homeserver.tailea48bb.ts.net:443 site (Jellyfin). It reuses the same
# Tailscale cert, so browsers still trust it and iPhone camera scanning works
# (HTTPS is required — CLAUDE.md decisions 4 & 7). Reachable at:
#     https://uk-homeserver.tailea48bb.ts.net:8443/
#
# Caddy runs as a host-networked container, so it binds host port 8443 directly
# and reaches the POS container through its published host port 5050. The cert
# is read from /etc/caddy/certs (already bind-mounted into Caddy).
#
# If 8443 (or 5050) is already used by another container, change the number
# here — and give the shop devices the matching URL.
# ============================================================================

uk-homeserver.tailea48bb.ts.net:8443 {
    tls /etc/caddy/certs/uk-homeserver.crt /etc/caddy/certs/uk-homeserver.key
    reverse_proxy localhost:5050
}
